  "description": "Ovule: the structure within a flower\u0026rsquo;s ovary that contains the female gametophyte (embryo sac) and develops into the seed after fertilization. The ovule is the female counterpart to the pollen grain, enclosing the egg cell, supporting tissues, and protective layers. Its development is simultaneous with pollen maturation in the anther, but ovule development is typically much slower and often stops at a specific stage until fertilization triggers resumption.\n¶Structure A mature ovule consists of several layers and regions:\n",
